videos.description: Oklahoma State's Cameron McGriff cleans up a missed layup and get the layup to fall for a potential 3-point play.
videos.headline: OSU's McGriff takes contact on putback layup

videos.description: West Virginia's Jevon Carter is left alone and drills the deep 3-pointer for the Mountaineers.
videos.headline: WVU's Carter nails 3-pointer

videos.description: West Virginia's Lamont West drains the open trey to keep a six-point cushion over Oklahoma State.
videos.headline: WVU's West nails clutch 3-pointer

videos.description: West Virginia's Sagaba Konate makes a ferocious block on Tavarius Shine with two hands.
videos.headline: WVU's Konate denies OSU's Shine with two hands

videos.description: WVU's Daxter Miles Jr. leads the fast break and finds Esa Ahmad on the alley-oop slam to send the Mountaineers crowd into a frenzy.
videos.headline: West Virginia connects on alley-oop

videos.description: Oklahoma State freshman Lindy Waters drains a wide-open 3-pointer to give the Cowboys a late 86-85 lead over the Mountaineers.
videos.headline: OSU's Waters III connects on game-winning 3

videos.description: OSU gets a steal and Jeffrey Carroll slams it home on the other end before Jevon Carter's 3-point shot misses as Oklahoma State beats West Virginia 88-85.
videos.headline: Carroll seals Oklahoma State upset with thunderous dunk
